Outliers distort an average value and a variety of measures obtained from them in the sample.

### Definition

A Node Game is a game involving two or more players that are represented symbolically on a graph. Each player has a color and a role, represented by a letter. Each color has a different strategy. They move along the edges of the graph (represented in a direction, either vertical, horizontal, or diagonal).
